            'body': 'In order to ensure a great experience connecting with Shopping Feed, please see your platform below for specific requirements needed.&nbsp;\r\n<h2>All platforms</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>Like most of the channels we connect to, we do not support more than two sets of variations for any product, usually reserved for&nbsp;<strong>Color&nbsp;&amp; Size.</strong>&nbsp;Most people recognize these variations as drop-down choice selections, found in major marketplaces like Amazon and Ebay. Any product that has more than two variation sets will not be compatible with the system, and will result in unsuccessful listings.</li>\r\n\t<li>\u200bUPC&#39;s, EAN&#39;s, or Barcodes are required by most major channels. We highly reccomend acquiring barcodes from your manufacturer, or the <a href="https://www.google.com/webhp?sourceid=chrome-instant&amp;ion=1&amp;espv=2&amp;ie=UTF-8#q=buy%20barcodes">purchase of your own barcodes.</a>&nbsp;Learn how to assign barcodes in <a href="https://help.shopify.com/manual/apps/apps-by-shopify/google-shopping/product-requirements#unique-product-identifiers">Shopify</a>, <a href="http://www.templatemonster.com/help/magento-how-to-create-an-attribute-and-apply-it-to-products.html#gref">Magento</a>, or <a href="http://doc.prestashop.com/display/PS15/Adding+Products+and+Product+Categories#AddingProductsandProductCategories-FillingouttheProductGlobalInformation">Prestashop</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class="sb sb-warning">\r\n<p class="sb-title">Warning</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Creating your own barcodes or using incorrect barcodes can result in your channel accounts to be penalized, and sometimes closed. Please use caution when assigning barcodes to your products.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Shopify</h2>\r\nTo list and sync properly, each product and variation to have a SKU, which we rely on internally as references in your account. If you have not assigned SKU&#39;s to your products in Shopify, we rely on the&nbsp;<a href="http://(https://help.shopify.com/themes/customization/products/find-variant-id">Shopify ID</a>&nbsp;as the SKU value by default. If you have assigned SKU&#39;s to your products and variations in Shopify, each of these SKU&#39;s must be unique.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h2>Prestashop</h2>\r\nAll product SKU&#39;s must be unique, including variations. To check this, we recommend downloading your products in a document to review SKU&#39;s.&nbsp;<a href="http://www.hostknox.com/tutorials/prestashop/1.5-1.6/export-and-import-data#export-information-from-prestashop">Find out more here</a>.\r\n\r\n<h2>Magento</h2>\r\nAll product&nbsp;SKU&#39;s must be unique, including variations. To check this,&nbsp;we recommend downloading your products in a document to review SKU&#39;s.&nbsp;<a href="https://lero9.co.nz/how-to-export-your-magento-product-database-using-using-magentos-importexport-dataflow-profiles/">Find out more here</a>',
            'body_email': 'In order to ensure a great experience connecting with Shopping Feed, please see your platform below for specific requirements needed. \n All platforms \n\n \n Like most of the channels we connect to, we do not support more than two sets of variations for any product, usually reserved for Color &amp; Size. Most people recognize these variations as drop-down choice selections, found in major marketplaces like Amazon and Ebay. Any product that has more than two variation sets will not be compatible with the system, and will result in unsuccessful listings. \n \u200bUPC\'s, EAN\'s, or Barcodes are required by most major channels. We highly reccomend acquiring barcodes from your manufacturer, or the purchase of your own barcodes. (https://www.google.com/webhp?sourceid=chrome-instant&amp;ion=1&amp;espv=2&amp;ie=UTF-8#q=buy%20barcodes) Learn how to assign barcodes in Shopify (https://help.shopify.com/manual/apps/apps-by-shopify/google-shopping/product-requirements#unique-product-identifiers), Magento (http://www.templatemonster.com/help/magento-how-to-create-an-attribute-and-apply-it-to-products.html#gref), or Prestashop (http://doc.prestashop.com/display/PS15/Adding+Products+and+Product+Categories#AddingProductsandProductCategories-FillingouttheProductGlobalInformation). \n \n\n \n Warning\n\nCreating your own barcodes or using incorrect barcodes can result in your channel accounts to be penalized, and sometimes closed. Please use caution when assigning barcodes to your products. \n \n\n Shopify \nTo list and sync properly, each product and variation to have a SKU, which we rely on internally as references in your account. If you have not assigned SKU\'s to your products in Shopify, we rely on the Shopify ID (http://(https://help.shopify.com/themes/customization/products/find-variant-id) as the SKU value by default. If you have assigned SKU\'s to your products and variations in Shopify, each of these SKU\'s must be unique. \n\n Prestashop \nAll product SKU\'s must be unique, including variations. To check this, we recommend downloading your products in a document to review SKU\'s. Find out more here (http://www.hostknox.com/tutorials/prestashop/1.5-1.6/export-and-import-data#export-information-from-prestashop).\n\n Magento \nAll product SKU\'s must be unique, including variations. To check this, we recommend downloading your products in a document to review SKU\'s. Find out more here (https://lero9.co.nz/how-to-export-your-magento-product-database-using-using-magentos-importexport-dataflow-profiles/)',
            'body_email_auto': true,
