            'locale': null,
            'subject': 'Ebay Pro Tips',
            'body': '<h2>Ebay Seller Limits</h2>\r\n<br />\r\nNew accounts are often restricted by <a href="http://pages.ebay.com/help/sell/sellinglimits.html">seller limits</a>.&nbsp;These limits prevent you from listing more than a certain number of individual SKU&#39;s, or more than a certain total inventory cost. To to compensate for eBay&#39;s Seller limitations, by default <a href="https://app.shopping-feed.com/tools/rules">a rule is created</a> that sends a quantity of 1 for all products that are in stock in your storefront. &nbsp;Instead of listing a higher quantity of the same product, we allow you to list a larger variety of products with a smaller quantity.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo make changes to this limitations, you can find and turn off this rule from <a href="https://app.shopping-feed.com/tools/rules">the rules page</a>. You can also <a href="https://scgi.ebay.com/ws/eBayISAPI.dll?UpgradeLimits">request a seller limit increase</a>&nbsp;in your Ebay account.',
            'body_email': 'Ebay Seller Limits \n\nNew accounts are often restricted by seller limits (http://pages.ebay.com/help/sell/sellinglimits.html). These limits prevent you from listing more than a certain number of individual SKU\'s, or more than a certain total inventory cost. To to compensate for eBay\'s Seller limitations, by default a rule is created (https://app.shopping-feed.com/tools/rules) that sends a quantity of 1 for all products that are in stock in your storefront.  Instead of listing a higher quantity of the same product, we allow you to list a larger variety of products with a smaller quantity.\n\nTo make changes to this limitations, you can find and turn off this rule from the rules page (https://app.shopping-feed.com/tools/rules). You can also request a seller limit increase (https://scgi.ebay.com/ws/eBayISAPI.dll?UpgradeLimits) in your Ebay account.',
            'body_email_auto': true,
            'body_chat': 'Ebay Seller Limits New accounts are often restricted by seller limits. These limits prevent you from listing more than a certain number of individual SKU\'s, or more than a certain total inventory cost. To to compensate for eBay\'s Seller limitations, ... https://support.shopping-feed.com/customer/portal/articles/2671386-ebay-pro-tips',
            'body_chat_auto': true,
            'body_web_callback': '<h2>Ebay Seller Limits</h2>\r\n<br />\r\nNew accounts are often restricted by <a href="http://pages.ebay.com/help/sell/sellinglimits.html">seller limits</a>.&nbsp;These limits prevent you from listing more than a certain number of individual SKU&#39;s, or more than a certain total inventory cost. To to compensate for eBay&#39;s Seller limitations, by default <a href="https://app.shopping-feed.com/tools/rules">a rule is created</a> that sends a quantity of 1 for all products that are in stock in your storefront. &nbsp;Instead of listing a higher quantity of the same product, we allow you to list a larger variety of products with a smaller quantity.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo make changes to this limitations, you can find and turn off this rule from <a href="https://app.shopping-feed.com/tools/rules">the rules page</a>. You can also <a href="https://scgi.ebay.com/ws/eBayISAPI.dll?UpgradeLimits">request a seller limit increase</a>&nbsp;in your Ebay account.',
            'body_web_callback_auto': true,
            'body_twitter': 'Ebay Seller Limits   New accounts are often restricted by seller limits. These limits prevent you from listing mo... https://support.shopping-feed.com/customer/portal/articles/2671386-ebay-pro-tips',
            'body_twitter_auto': true,
            'body_qna': 'Ebay Seller Limits \n\nNew accounts are often restricted by seller limits. These limits prevent you from listing more than a certain number of individual SKU\'s, or more than a certain total inventory cost. To to compensate for eBay\'s Seller limitations, by default a rule is created that sends a quantity of 1 for all products that are in stock in your storefront.  Instead of listing a higher quantity of the same product, we allow you to list a larger variety of products with a smaller quantity.\n\nTo make changes to this limitations, you can find and turn off this rule from the rules page. You can also request a seller limit increase in your Ebay account.',
            'body_qna_auto': true,
            'body_phone': 'Ebay Seller Limits \n\nNew accounts are often restricted by seller limits. These limits prevent you from listing more than a certain number of individual SKU\'s, or more than a certain total inventory cost. To to compensate for eBay\'s Seller limitations, by default a rule is created that sends a quantity of 1 for all products that are in stock in your storefront.  Instead of listing a higher quantity of the same product, we allow you to list a larger variety of products with a smaller quantity.\n\nTo make changes to this limitations, you can find and turn off this rule from the rules page. You can also request a seller limit increase in your Ebay account.',
            'body_phone_auto': true,
            'body_facebook': 'Ebay Seller Limits \n\nNew accounts are often restricted by seller limits. These limits prevent you from listing more than a certain number of individual SKU\'s, or more than a certain total inventory cost. To to compensate for eBay\'s Seller limitations, by default a rule is created that sends a quantity of 1 for all products that are in stock in your storefront.  Instead of listing a higher quantity of the same product, we allow you to list a larger variety of products with a smaller quantity.\n\nTo make changes to this limitations, you can find and turn off this rule from the rules page. You can also request a seller limit increase in your Ebay account.',
